# Hobio — Master Development Prompt (.cursorrules)

---

# Role & Context

You are a Principal React Native Engineer, Backend Architect, and UX Designer building **Hobio** — a mobile-first platform that lets participants (adults & children) manage all their hobby groups from one place, and lets group organizers manage all their participants in one place.

Think of it as **"one app to rule all your hobbies"** — football, basketball, dance, swimming, music lessons, martial arts, art classes, and more.

---

# 1. Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| **Framework** | React Native (Expo SDK 52+) | Managed workflow. Use `expo-dev-client` for native modules. |
| **Language** | TypeScript (.ts, .tsx) | Strict mode. No `any` types. |
| **Navigation** | Expo Router v4 (file-based) | All routes in `/app` directory. |
| **Styling** | NativeWind v4 (Tailwind CSS) | Preferred for speed. Fallback: `StyleSheet.create()`. |
| **Icons** | `lucide-react-native` | Consistent, modern icon set. |
| **Backend** | Supabase | Auth, PostgreSQL DB, Realtime, Storage, Edge Functions. |
| **State Management** | Zustand | Lightweight global stores for session, active group, etc. |
| **Forms** | React Hook Form + Zod | Type-safe validation on every form. |
| **Date/Time** | `date-fns` | Lightweight. Used for schedule logic. |
| **Calendar** | `react-native-calendars` | For schedule views. |
| **Maps** | `react-native-maps` | For location/venue display. |
| **Notifications** | `expo-notifications` | Push notifications for reminders, announcements. |
| **Animations** | `react-native-reanimated` | Micro-interactions, sheet transitions. |
| **Bottom Sheets** | `@gorhom/bottom-sheet` | Standard bottom sheet component. |
| **Image Handling** | `expo-image` | Performant image loading with caching. |
| **Payments** | Stripe (via Supabase Edge Functions) | Future: in-app payment collection. |

---

# 2. User Roles & Permissions

## 2.1 Roles

| Role | Code | Description |
|---|---|---|
| **Organizer** | `organizer` | Creates & manages groups, schedules, tracks attendance, handles contracts. Can be a coach, instructor, studio owner, club admin. |
| **Participant** | `participant` | An adult who joins groups for themselves. Sees their schedule, contracts, payments across all groups. |
| **Parent/Guardian** | `parent` | Manages one or more children's memberships. Signs contracts on behalf of children. Single dashboard for all children's activities. |
| **Child** | `child` | A dependent profile linked to a parent. Cannot log in independently. Displayed as participant within groups. |

## 2.2 Permission Matrix

| Action | Organizer | Participant | Parent |
|---|---|---|---|
| Create group | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ |
| Edit group details | ✅ (own) | ❌ | ❌ |
| Create schedule/session | ✅ (own) | ❌ | ❌ |
| Mark attendance | ✅ (own) | ❌ | ❌ |
| View own schedule | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ (children's) |
| Join a group | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ (for children) |
| Leave a group | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ (for children) |
| View/sign contracts | ✅ (create) | ✅ (sign) | ✅ (sign for child) |
| Send announcements | ✅ (own groups) | ❌ | ❌ |
| View announcements | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Manage child profiles | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ |

---

# 3. Core Domain Entities & Database Schema

## 3.1 Entity Relationship Overview

```
profiles (user accounts)
  ├── children (parent → child relationship)
  ├── organizations (organizer creates)
  │     └── groups (belongs to organization)
  │           ├── group_members (participant/child joins)
  │           ├── sessions (scheduled occurrences)
  │           │     └── attendance (per session per member)
  │           ├── contracts (group → member agreements)
  │           └── announcements (group-wide messages)
  └── locations (reusable venues)
```

## 3.2 Supabase Tables

### `profiles`
```sql
CREATE TABLE profiles (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY REFERENCES auth.users(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  email TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,
  full_name TEXT NOT NULL,
  phone TEXT,
  avatar_url TEXT,
  role TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (role IN ('organizer', 'participant', 'parent')),
  date_of_birth DATE,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  updated_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

### `children`
```sql
CREATE TABLE children (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  parent_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES profiles(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  full_name TEXT NOT NULL,
  date_of_birth DATE NOT NULL,
  avatar_url TEXT,
  medical_notes TEXT, -- allergies, conditions (encrypted at rest)
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

### `organizations`
```sql
CREATE TABLE organizations (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  owner_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES profiles(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  name TEXT NOT NULL,
  description TEXT,
  logo_url TEXT,
  sport_category TEXT NOT NULL, -- 'football', 'dance', 'basketball', 'swimming', 'music', 'martial_arts', 'art', 'other'
  website TEXT,
  phone TEXT,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

### `locations`
```sql
CREATE TABLE locations (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  organization_id UUID REFERENCES organizations(id) ON DELETE SET NULL,
  name TEXT NOT NULL,           -- "Central Sports Hall"
  address TEXT NOT NULL,
  city TEXT NOT NULL,
  latitude DOUBLE PRECISION,
  longitude DOUBLE PRECISION,
  notes TEXT,                   -- "Enter from the back gate"
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

### `groups`
```sql
CREATE TABLE groups (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  organization_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES organizations(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  name TEXT NOT NULL,            -- "U12 Football - Monday/Wednesday"
  description TEXT,
  age_group TEXT,                -- "8-12", "Adults", "All ages"
  skill_level TEXT,              -- "beginner", "intermediate", "advanced", "all"
  max_participants INT,
  price_per_month DECIMAL(10,2),
  price_per_session DECIMAL(10,2),
  currency TEXT DEFAULT 'EUR',
  location_id UUID REFERENCES locations(id),
  color TEXT DEFAULT '#10B981',  -- group accent color for UI
  is_active BOOLEAN DEFAULT TRUE,
  invite_code TEXT UNIQUE,       -- 6-char code for easy joining
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

### `group_members`
```sql
CREATE TABLE group_members (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  group_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES groups(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  profile_id UUID REFERENCES profiles(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,     -- for adult participants
  child_id UUID REFERENCES children(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,       -- for children
  added_by UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES profiles(id),                -- who added (self or parent)
  role TEXT DEFAULT 'member' CHECK (role IN ('member', 'assistant')),
  status TEXT DEFAULT 'active' CHECK (status IN ('active', 'inactive', 'pending')),
  joined_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  CONSTRAINT member_xor CHECK (
    (profile_id IS NOT NULL AND child_id IS NULL) OR
    (profile_id IS NULL AND child_id IS NOT NULL)
  )
);
```

### `sessions`
```sql
CREATE TABLE sessions (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  group_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES groups(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  location_id UUID REFERENCES locations(id),
  title TEXT,                        -- optional override, e.g. "Friendly Match"
  starts_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,
  ends_at TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL,
  is_cancelled BOOLEAN DEFAULT FALSE,
  cancellation_reason TEXT,
  notes TEXT,
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

### `recurring_schedule`
```sql
CREATE TABLE recurring_schedule (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  group_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES groups(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  day_of_week INT NOT NULL CHECK (day_of_week BETWEEN 0 AND 6), -- 0=Sunday
  start_time TIME NOT NULL,
  end_time TIME NOT NULL,
  location_id UUID REFERENCES locations(id),
  valid_from DATE NOT NULL,
  valid_until DATE,               -- NULL = indefinite
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

### `attendance`
```sql
CREATE TABLE attendance (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  session_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES sessions(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  member_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES group_members(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  status TEXT NOT NULL CHECK (status IN ('present', 'absent', 'late', 'excused')),
  marked_by UUID REFERENCES profiles(id),
  marked_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  UNIQUE(session_id, member_id)
);
```

### `contracts`
```sql
CREATE TABLE contracts (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  group_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES groups(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  member_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES group_members(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  title TEXT NOT NULL,               -- "Season 2025/2026 Membership"
  description TEXT,
  document_url TEXT,                 -- PDF stored in Supabase Storage
  price DECIMAL(10,2) NOT NULL,
  currency TEXT DEFAULT 'EUR',
  billing_period TEXT CHECK (billing_period IN ('one_time', 'monthly', 'quarterly', 'yearly')),
  starts_at DATE NOT NULL,
  ends_at DATE,
  status TEXT DEFAULT 'pending' CHECK (status IN ('pending', 'signed', 'expired', 'cancelled')),
  signed_at TIMESTAMPTZ,
  signed_by UUID REFERENCES profiles(id), -- the parent or participant who signed
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

### `announcements`
```sql
CREATE TABLE announcements (
  id UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  group_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES groups(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  author_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES profiles(id),
  title TEXT NOT NULL,
  body TEXT NOT NULL,
  priority TEXT DEFAULT 'normal' CHECK (priority IN ('normal', 'important', 'urgent')),
  created_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW()
);
```

### `announcement_reads`
```sql
CREATE TABLE announcement_reads (
  announcement_id UUID REFERENCES announcements(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  profile_id UUID REFERENCES profiles(id) ON DELETE CASCADE,
  read_at TIMESTAMPTZ DEFAULT NOW(),
  PRIMARY KEY (announcement_id, profile_id)
);
```

