# 7. Coding Standards

## 7.1 Strict Mobile-Only
- **NEVER** use `<div>`, `<span>`, `<img>`, `<button>`, or any HTML element.
- **ALWAYS** use `<View>`, `<Text>`, `<Image>`, `<Pressable>`, `<TouchableOpacity>`, `<ScrollView>`, `<FlatList>`.
- **ALWAYS** wrap screen roots in `<SafeAreaView>` from `react-native-safe-area-context`.

## 7.2 Component Architecture
```
src/
├── components/
│   ├── ui/                 # Reusable primitives (Button, Input, Card, Avatar, Badge)
│   ├── groups/             # Group-related components (GroupCard, MemberRow)
│   ├── schedule/           # Schedule components (SessionCard, CalendarDay)
│   ├── attendance/         # Attendance components (AttendanceRow, StatusBadge)
│   └── layout/             # Layout wrappers (ScreenWrapper, FloatingTabBar)
├── hooks/                  # Custom hooks (useGroups, useSessions, useAuth)
├── stores/                 # Zustand stores (authStore, groupStore)
├── lib/                    # Utilities (supabase client, date helpers, constants)
├── types/                  # TypeScript interfaces & types (database.types.ts)
└── constants/              # Colors, spacing, sport categories
```

## 7.3 TypeScript Standards
- Every component has a typed `interface Props { ... }`.
- Generate Supabase types: `npx supabase gen types typescript --project-id <id> > src/types/database.types.ts`.
- Use `z.infer<typeof schema>` for form types.
- No `any`. Use `unknown` + type guards when type is uncertain.

## 7.4 Data Fetching
- Use custom hooks per entity: `useGroups()`, `useSessions()`, `useMembers(groupId)`.
- Each hook uses `useEffect` + `useState` for loading/error/data pattern.
- Future: Migrate to TanStack Query (React Query) for caching & background refetching.

## 7.5 File Naming
- Components: `PascalCase.tsx` (e.g., `GroupCard.tsx`).
- Hooks: `camelCase.ts` (e.g., `useGroups.ts`).
- Utilities: `camelCase.ts` (e.g., `dateHelpers.ts`).
- Types: `camelCase.ts` (e.g., `database.types.ts`).
- Screens (in `/app`): `kebab-case.tsx` as per Expo Router convention.

---

# 8. Feature Details & Business Logic

## 8.1 Invite Code System
- When a group is created, generate a 6-character alphanumeric code (uppercase, no ambiguous chars: exclude 0/O, 1/I/L).
- Characters: `ABCDEFGHJKMNPQRSTUVWXYZ23456789`
- Participants enter the code manually or scan a QR code containing a deep link: `hobio://join/{code}`
- On join: Check if group exists → Show group preview (name, org, sport, schedule) → Confirm → Create `group_members` entry.

## 8.2 Recurring Schedule → Session Generation
- Organizers define recurring schedules (e.g., "Every Monday 17:00-18:30").
- A Supabase Edge Function (or cron) generates `sessions` rows 4 weeks ahead.
- Organizers can also create one-off sessions manually.
- Cancelled sessions stay in DB with `is_cancelled = true` and a reason.

## 8.3 Attendance Logic
- For each session, auto-create attendance rows for all active group members with status `null` (unmarked).
- Organizer opens session → sees member list → taps each to toggle: present ✅ / absent ❌ / late ⏰ / excused 📝.
- After marking, parents receive a push notification summary: "Alex was marked present at Football today."

## 8.4 Contract Lifecycle
1. **Draft**: Organizer creates contract with title, description, price, period, optional PDF.
2. **Pending**: Assigned to member(s). Appears in their Contracts tab.
3. **Signed**: Participant or parent digitally signs (tap-to-sign, stored timestamp + signer ID).
4. **Expired/Cancelled**: Auto-expire based on `ends_at` or manual cancellation.

## 8.5 Announcements & Notifications
- Organizer writes an announcement scoped to a group.
- All group members (and parents of child members) receive a push notification.
- In-app: unread badge on Notifications tab. Read status tracked in `announcement_reads`.
- Priority levels affect notification styling: `urgent` = red banner at top of group screen.

## 8.6 Dashboard Logic (Home Screen)

### Organizer Dashboard
- **Today's Sessions**: List of sessions happening today across all their groups.
- **Quick Stats**: Total members, attendance rate this week, pending contracts.
- **Recent Activity**: Latest joins, contract signatures, attendance completions.

### Participant Dashboard
- **My Schedule Today**: Sessions they're part of, with time and location.
- **Upcoming This Week**: Next 7 days of sessions.
- **Unread Announcements**: Latest announcements badge.

### Parent Dashboard
- **Child Switcher**: Horizontal scroll of child avatars at top. "All" option.
- **Today's Schedule**: Merged schedule of selected child (or all children).
- **Pending Actions**: Unsigned contracts, unread announcements.

---

# 9. Supabase Configuration

## 9.1 Row Level Security (RLS) Policies
Enable RLS on ALL tables. Key policies:

- `profiles`: Users can read any profile. Users can update only their own.
- `children`: Only the parent (`parent_id = auth.uid()`) can CRUD.
- `organizations`: Anyone can read. Only owner can update/delete.
- `groups`: Anyone can read active groups. Only org owner can update.
- `group_members`: Members can read their own group's members. Org owner can CRUD.
- `sessions`: Group members can read. Org owner can CRUD.
- `attendance`: Org owner can CRUD. Members can read their own.
- `contracts`: Org owner can create. Member/parent can read & update (sign) their own.
- `announcements`: Group members can read. Org owner can create.

## 9.2 Realtime Subscriptions
- Subscribe to `announcements` table for live announcement feed.
- Subscribe to `sessions` table for live cancellation updates.
- Subscribe to `attendance` table for real-time attendance marking (organizer screen).

## 9.3 Storage Buckets
- `avatars` — Profile and child photos. Public read, authenticated write (own).
- `logos` — Organization logos. Public read, org owner write.
- `contracts` — PDF documents. Authenticated read (member/owner), org owner write.

