# 11. Performance & Quality Guidelines

1. **Lists**: Always use `<FlatList>` for lists > 10 items. Never map inside `<ScrollView>` for long lists.
2. **Images**: Use `expo-image` with `placeholder` prop for blur-up loading.
3. **Memoization**: Use `React.memo()` on list item components. Use `useMemo`/`useCallback` for expensive computations and callback props.
4. **Skeleton Loading**: Show skeleton placeholders while data loads. Never show blank screens.
5. **Error Boundaries**: Wrap each tab in an error boundary with retry option.
6. **Offline Awareness**: Show a subtle banner when offline. Queue writes and sync when back online (future).
7. **Accessibility**: All touchable elements need `accessibilityLabel`. Use `accessibilityRole` on buttons.

---

# 12. Testing Strategy

- **Unit Tests**: Jest + React Native Testing Library for component logic.
- **Integration Tests**: Test Supabase hooks with mocked client.
- **E2E Tests**: Detox or Maestro for critical flows (sign up, join group, mark attendance).
- **Type Safety**: `tsc --noEmit` in CI to catch type errors.

---

# 13. Environment Variables

```env
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://xxx.supabase.co
EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...
EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=AIza...
```

Never commit `.env` files. Use EAS Secrets for production builds.

---

# 14. Implementation Priority (Build Order)

### Phase 1 — Foundation (MVP)
1. Project setup (Expo, NativeWind, Supabase client)
2. Auth flow (sign up, sign in, forgot password)
3. Onboarding (role selection, basic profile setup)
4. Group CRUD (create, read, update for organizers)
5. Invite code join flow
6. Basic group member list
7. Tab navigation with role-based dashboard shells

### Phase 2 — Core Features
8. Recurring schedule setup + session generation
9. Unified calendar view (all groups, color-coded)
10. Attendance marking (organizer)
11. Attendance viewing (participant/parent)
12. Child profile management (parent role)
13. Parent dashboard with child switcher

### Phase 3 — Engagement
14. Announcements (create, read, push notifications)
15. Contract creation and digital signing
16. Location/venue display with maps
17. Session cancellation with reason + notification
18. Notification center

### Phase 4 — Polish
19. Empty states with illustrations
20. Skeleton loading screens
21. Pull-to-refresh everywhere
22. Animations (page transitions, attendance toggle)
23. QR code generation & scanning for invite codes
24. Dark mode support

### Phase 5 — Monetization & Scale
25. Stripe payment integration
26. Attendance reports & statistics
27. Export data (CSV/PDF)
28. Multi-language support (i18n)
29. Offline mode
30. App Store & Play Store submission
